# UX Documentation Index

This directory contains comprehensive user experience planning documentation for the American Mahjong application. These documents focus on **user behavior, information architecture, performance constraints, and design decisions** rather than implementation details.

---

## Quick Navigation

 | Document | Purpose | When to Read |
 | ---------- | --------- | -------------- |
 | [User Journeys](user-journeys.md) | Critical user paths through the app | Before designing screens |
 | [Edge Cases](edge-cases.md) | Error scenarios and non-happy paths | During implementation & testing |
 | [Interaction States](interaction-states.md) | Component behavior reference | When building UI components |
 | [Mobile Constraints](mobile-constraints.md) | Mobile-specific design solutions | When implementing responsive UI |

---

## Document Summaries

### 1. [User Journeys](user-journeys.md)

**What it covers**:

- 5 detailed user journeys with step-by-step flows

- Information architecture decisions (what to show, when)

- Emotional state tracking (where users get frustrated)

- Critical dropout risk points

- UX intervention recommendations

**Key Journeys**:

1. **First-Time Player** - Tutorial needs, onboarding flow (highest dropout risk at "The Card")

1. **Experienced Player** - Fast-paced competitive play, keyboard shortcuts, pattern viability tracker

1. **Mobile User** - One-handed play, reconnection, thumb-zone constraints

1. **Screen Reader User** - Audio navigation, condensed mode, timing adjustments

1. **Disconnection Recovery** - Mid-Charleston disconnect, AI takeover, rejoining

**Use this when**: Designing screen flows, prioritizing features, understanding user pain points.

---

### 2. [Edge Cases & Error Scenarios](edge-cases.md)

**What it covers**:

- 37 edge cases across 8 categories

- Expected behavior for each scenario

- User impact analysis

- UX solutions (modals, toasts, error messages)

- Testing strategy

**Categories**:

1. Authentication & Session Management (3 cases)

1. Lobby & Matchmaking (3 cases)

1. Charleston Phase (5 cases) ⚠️ Most complex

1. Playing Phase (5 cases)

1. Network & Connectivity (5 cases)

1. Scoring & Game Over (3 cases)

1. Mobile-Specific (3 cases)

1. Accessibility (2 cases)

**Severity Levels**:

- 🔴 **Critical** (12 cases): Must fix for MVP

- 🟡 **Major** (15 cases): 8 for MVP, 7 post-MVP

- 🟢 **Minor** (10 cases): 2 for MVP, 8 post-MVP

**Use this when**: Handling errors, testing features, designing error messages, preventing user frustration.

