## How to Use This Documentation

### For Product/UX Design

**Start here**: [User Journeys](user-journeys.md)

- Understand user needs and pain points

- Identify critical UX interventions (tutorial, hints, pattern tracker)

- Prioritize features based on dropout risk

**Then review**: [Mobile Constraints](mobile-constraints.md)

- Learn screen size and touch constraints

- Design with progressive disclosure in mind

### For Frontend Implementation

**Start here**: [Interaction States](interaction-states.md)

- Reference state matrix when building components

- Follow accessibility requirements (ARIA labels, keyboard nav)

- Match animation timings

**Then review**: [Edge Cases](edge-cases.md)

- Implement error handling for each scenario

- Test against defined expected behaviors

### For QA/Testing

**Start here**: [Edge Cases](edge-cases.md)

- Test all 37 documented scenarios

- Verify error messages match specifications

- Check severity-based priority (🔴 critical first)

**Then review**: [Interaction States](interaction-states.md)

- Verify all component states render correctly

- Test keyboard navigation and screen reader announcements

### For Mobile Development

**Start here**: [Mobile Constraints](mobile-constraints.md)

- Understand space budgets and touch targets

- Implement thumb-zone button placement

- Test on 375×667px minimum (iPhone SE)

**Then review**: [User Journeys](user-journeys.md) - Journey 3 (Mobile User)

- Follow mobile-specific journey steps

- Implement reconnection flow

