## Key Insights from UX Research

### Highest Dropout Risk Points

1. **First-time player sees "The Card"** (Journey 1, Step 19) - 60% abandon rate expected

   - **Solution**: Hint system + pattern highlighting

1. **Charleston first-time experience** (Journey 1, Step 9) - 30% abandon without tutorial

   - **Solution**: Onboarding overlay with directional arrows

1. **Mobile thumb reachability** (Journey 3, Step 2) - 30% frustration rate

   - **Solution**: Bottom-third button placement

### Most Requested Features (Experienced Players)

1. **Pattern Viability Tracker** - Auto-gray impossible patterns (all 4 tiles out)

1. **Keyboard Shortcuts** - Spacebar to confirm, C to call, P to pass

1. **Instant Replay** - Timeline scrubbing to review key moments

1. **Fast Play Mode** - Disable animations, 30s timers

### Critical Mobile Challenges

1. **Information Density** - Can't fit all game info on 375px width

   - **Solution**: Progressive disclosure (modals for Card, discard pile)

1. **Tile Selection** - 13 tiles don't fit on screen

   - **Solution**: Horizontal scroll + selection preview area

1. **One-Handed Use** - Top buttons unreachable

   - **Solution**: Thumb-zone layout (actions at bottom)

### Accessibility Requirements

1. **Screen Reader Support** - Every visual state has audio equivalent

1. **Condensed Audio Mode** - "Bamboo: 1, 2, 3" instead of "1 Bamboo, 2 Bamboo, 3 Bamboo"

1. **Extended Timers** - 2x time for screen reader users (120s turn timer)

1. **Keyboard-Only Navigation** - All actions accessible without mouse

